&lt;li&gt;Full-time, 40 hours per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evening and weekend availability required based on business needs and the team’s canvassing schedule&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This position requires regular travel throughout the Bay Area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Requirements Include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid California Driver’s License&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean driving record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable transportation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supervisory Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and support the Bay Area MDU Growth team in achieving individual and team sales goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ongoing coaching, mentorship, and field development for team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct side-by-side selling and in-field observations to improve sales effectiveness and customer engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of accountability, teamwork, professionalism, and continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support onboarding and training efforts for new hires and developing representatives&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
