&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet Monthly sales performance expectations and Drive Take Rate at Full Building Installs to 30%&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete at least 200 knocked doors and 3 new orders per day through door hangers and door knocking.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate onsite events with landlords and property managers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visit Full Building Installs during installation coordinating with Acquisition team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check the regular dispatch calendar for standard single-unit installations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize Salesforce Maps for efficient marketing routes and track doors knocked per day.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leave marketing materials behind and send emails to online community groups.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record and update opportunities daily in Directly and Salesforce.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow a weekly schedule with quality field activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide daily reports on scheduled visits and results to the Sales Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus on increasing Take Rate on Acquired Buildings. Use FBI excel sheet to attack lowest take rate buildings.&lt;/li&gt;
